1
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:37,900
<i> It's legit, right?</i>

2
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:39,367
<i>Aren't you still going
to invest?</i>

3
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:40,867
<i> I've already invested in it.</i>

4
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,033
<i> Why are you in a rush?</i>

5
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:43,267
<i> You know why.</i>

6
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:45,667
<i>Come on, Andrea,
I just don't want your success</i>

7
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,767
<i>to be driven by your anger
at your mother.</i>

8
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:49,533
<i>You should do it
because you like it.</i>

9
00:00:49,833 --> 00:00:51,333
<i> Daisy, I need money for fare.</i>

10
00:00:51,467 --> 00:00:53,600
<i>Jeff, I'm not
complaining, but...</i>

11
00:00:53,733 --> 00:00:55,867
<i>I know I'm already
a burden to you.</i>

12
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,800
<i>I promise, I'll have work
when I come back later.</i>

13
00:00:57,933 --> 00:00:59,233
<i> Daisy was right, bro.</i>

14
00:00:59,367 --> 00:01:00,767
<i>Why don't you go back
to Auntie Felma?</i>

15
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:02,667
<i>If that's all you have to say,
I'm going home.</i>

16
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:03,900
<i>I'm just giving you a real talk.</i>

17
00:01:04,033 --> 00:01:06,033
<i>What's the job you're talking
about? Any update?</i>

18
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:08,300
<i> Boss, I'm here with my friend.</i>

19
00:01:08,467 --> 00:01:09,900
<i>The one I was hoping to
recommend to Shop Point.</i>

20
00:01:10,033 --> 00:01:11,133
<i>He rides the motorcycle, right?</i>

21
00:01:11,267 --> 00:01:13,200
<i>- I know how to motorcycle.
- Okay, you're hired.</i>

22
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:14,400
<i> Thank you, Felma.</i>

23
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:16,100
<i>I honestly don't know
how I'm going</i>

24
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:17,433
<i> to face all this without you.</i>

25
00:01:17,567 --> 00:01:19,233
<i>Are you ready to talk
about the case</i>

26
00:01:19,367 --> 00:01:20,667
<i>we're going to file
against your wife?</i>

27
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:22,067
<i> Yes, Attorney.</i>

28
00:01:23,867 --> 00:01:25,033
<i>- Hazel?
- Hazel?</i>

29
00:01:25,167 --> 00:01:26,200
<i> Manuel, I'm begging you.</i>

30
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:28,733
<i>I only want to ask
for our daughter's forgiveness.</i>

31
00:01:28,867 --> 00:01:30,900
<i> I'm so sorry, Dear.</i>

32
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:33,900
<i> Please forgive me.</i>

33
00:01:34,033 --> 00:01:36,633
<i>Mommy, please stop harassing
Auntie Felma.</i>

34
00:01:36,767 --> 00:01:38,833
<i> Let Dad and me be for now.</i>

35
00:01:38,967 --> 00:01:42,767
<i>Can we just settle this without
going to court?</i>

36
00:01:42,933 --> 00:01:44,433
<i> The truth finally comes out.</i>

37
00:01:44,567 --> 00:01:47,367
<i>You're only pleading for me
to drop the case.</i>

38
00:01:47,967 --> 00:01:50,300
<i>Dad, please, I don't want
any more trouble</i>

39
00:01:50,433 --> 00:01:52,367
<i>I don't want to tell
someone else</i>

40
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:54,733
<i> about our problems.</i>

41
00:01:54,867 --> 00:01:56,633
<i> You helped your own enemy.</i>

42
00:01:56,767 --> 00:01:58,033
<i> You really are unbelievable.</i>

43
00:01:58,167 --> 00:01:59,433
<i>If she does mess with them
again,</i>

44
00:01:59,567 --> 00:02:01,933
<i>she really could lose her child.</i>

45
00:02:02,067 --> 00:02:05,500
<i>So, if that happens?
You'll be Jessica's mother?</i>

46
00:02:05,633 --> 00:02:09,367
<i>You have children
who need your attention more.</i>

47
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:11,100
<i> Where's mom, Didang?</i>

48
00:02:11,233 --> 00:02:13,467
<i> Maybe Jessica still needs her.</i>

49
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,733
<i>She has a daughter
waiting for her.</i>

50
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:19,000
<i>Where is that jealousy towards
Jessica coming from?</i>

51
00:02:20,133 --> 00:02:23,000
<i>- It says something else.
- I'm just a little hurt by mom.</i>

52
00:02:23,133 --> 00:02:24,933
<i>It feels like
she's forgetting me.</i>

53
00:02:25,067 --> 00:02:26,967
<i>I'm taking a break
from bothering my family.</i>

54
00:02:27,100 --> 00:02:28,333
<i> Let's focus on her.</i>

55
00:02:28,467 --> 00:02:31,133
<i> There, that longganisa vendor.</i>

56
00:02:36,167 --> 00:02:37,167
It's an emergency, Sis.

57
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:38,333
It's unexpected.

58
00:02:38,467 --> 00:02:39,800
Tetay needs it in school.

59
00:02:39,933 --> 00:02:41,533
Is there any money
you could spare?

60
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:45,233
Okay, okay.

61
00:02:45,367 --> 00:02:47,033
- Thank you, bye.
- Daisy!

62
00:02:49,033 --> 00:02:49,800
Whose is that?

63
00:02:49,933 --> 00:02:50,967
Ours.

64
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:53,700
There.

65
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:54,867
How did you get that?

66
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,267
And what for?

67
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:59,267
Jopet helped me
with the down payment.

68
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:02,333
Then he helped me get a job at
Shop Point Express.

69
00:03:02,467 --> 00:03:04,700
I'll work as a rider for now.

70
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:08,367
So please stop pushing me
to return to FMP and to mom.

71
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:09,633
Here it is.

72
00:03:09,767 --> 00:03:11,133
Rider?

73
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,067
That's dangerous.

74
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,567
Do you know how to ride
a motorcycle?

75
00:03:16,767 --> 00:03:18,433
I managed to come home.

76
00:03:18,567 --> 00:03:20,067
And it's easy to learn.

77
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,733
My license is both code A and B.

78
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:23,633
I can drive cars
and motorcycles.

79
00:03:26,433 --> 00:03:27,967
Here we go again, Daisy.

80
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:29,467
Why can't you just be happy?

81
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:30,800
I'm trying my best.

82
00:03:32,933 --> 00:03:35,200
Why is it so hard for you
to support me?

83
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,067
Guys...

84
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:47,200
thank you for coming.

85
00:03:47,467 --> 00:03:50,000
And thank you for investing.

86
00:03:50,133 --> 00:03:52,500
I've got everything.

87
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:54,000
Thank you, Ma'am Andrea.

88
00:03:54,167 --> 00:03:56,167
I'm excited to earn money.

89
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:58,800
Me, too. But, Ma'am,
it's a sure bet, isn't it?

90
00:03:58,933 --> 00:04:01,800
I'll put all my savings into
this because I believe in you.

91
00:04:01,933 --> 00:04:05,100
I invested all my savings
as well.

92
00:04:05,233 --> 00:04:07,367
Don't worry, this is legit.

93
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:09,167
So, if you know anyone,

94
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:12,067
friends,
our colleagues from FMP,

95
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,633
who want to invest...

96
00:04:13,767 --> 00:04:15,500
We've already told some of them.

97
00:04:15,633 --> 00:04:18,267
I have a question, Ma'am.

98
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:19,700
When will you be back?

99
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:23,067
I'm no longer coming back.

100
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:25,033
I've already found a new job.

101
00:04:27,733 --> 00:04:30,367
How are you at FMP?

102
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,067
We're having a hard time, Ma'am.

103
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:33,300
It's so unorganized.

104
00:04:33,433 --> 00:04:36,600
Unlike when you were there,
we have a smooth workflow.

105
00:04:36,733 --> 00:04:40,067
And there are still
online bashers.

106
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:43,600
Those who believe Karla Talakera

107
00:04:43,733 --> 00:04:47,200
and Hazel's exposé
against Ma'am Felma.

108
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,600
Make sure you eat a lot.

109
00:04:56,733 --> 00:04:58,600
- I will.
- So you'll regain your strength

110
00:04:58,733 --> 00:05:00,267
- faster.
- Yes, and later...

111
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:03,000
you and Coleen
should go to bed early.

112
00:05:03,167 --> 00:05:04,900
So you can recover faster.

113
00:05:05,033 --> 00:05:06,633
- Okay?
- Okay.

114
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:07,633
Thank you.

115
00:05:07,767 --> 00:05:08,700
There you go.

116
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:10,367
Jessica?

117
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:12,233
- You're back home!
- Coleen!

118
00:05:16,167 --> 00:05:17,667
I missed you!

119
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:20,067
Oh, be careful.

120
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,200
We were supposed
to go home tomorrow.

121
00:05:22,333 --> 00:05:26,333
But I convinced dad and Auntie
Felma to go home today.

122
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:31,467
No one informed me.

123
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,467
Sweetie.

124
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,500
Oh, Dear.

125
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:35,700
Go on and eat.

126
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:36,767
Come here.

127
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:38,267
Go on, Jessica.

128
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,733
Sit down now.

129
00:05:39,867 --> 00:05:42,300
Then let's eat, Okay?

130
00:05:42,433 --> 00:05:43,800
Thank you.

131
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:53,100
Oh, that...

132
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:55,400
Shrimp paste, please.

133
00:05:55,533 --> 00:05:57,633
Thank you. Thank you.

134
00:05:57,767 --> 00:05:58,633
- Ma'am Felma.
- Oh?

135
00:05:58,767 --> 00:06:00,667
Daisy's outside.

136
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,433
Why doesn't she come in?

137
00:06:02,567 --> 00:06:04,433
Her ride is waiting for her.

138
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,500
Oh, okay, I'll go and see her.

139
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:09,600
Please excuse me,
keep on eating.

140
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:13,633
Go ahead and eat.

141
00:06:13,767 --> 00:06:14,933
Didang, please take care
of them.

142
00:06:15,067 --> 00:06:16,300
Yes, Ma'am.

143
00:06:20,267 --> 00:06:21,267
This is a lot.

144
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,333
There.

145
00:06:22,467 --> 00:06:23,933
What are you planning to do
with these?

146
00:06:24,067 --> 00:06:26,400
I want to take down FMP,
remember?

147
00:06:26,533 --> 00:06:28,100
Felma's company.

148
00:06:28,233 --> 00:06:29,600
We're going to start from here.

149
00:06:37,467 --> 00:06:39,000
What's that?

150
00:06:39,133 --> 00:06:41,033
Poison?

151
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,200
Of course not.

152
00:06:43,533 --> 00:06:46,000
This is a fast-acting laxative.

153
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:47,833
Not a poison.

154
00:06:47,967 --> 00:06:48,967
Food grade.

155
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:51,267
So don't worry.

156
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:53,967
But anyone who eats this...

157
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:58,833
will think they got
food poisoning.

158
00:06:58,967 --> 00:07:00,367
They?

159
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:01,567
Who's they?

160
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,800
Those homeless people
in Luntian Park.

161
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:08,400
You're joining a barangay
feeding program over there.

162
00:07:08,533 --> 00:07:11,700
Hazel, you're going to involve
even more people?

163
00:07:13,367 --> 00:07:15,367
So that the news spreads faster.

164
00:07:15,533 --> 00:07:17,067
So people will think

165
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:20,033
Flirty Felma's products
are contaminated.

166
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:23,300
Come on, Friend.

167
00:07:23,433 --> 00:07:26,267
Your anger will hurt many.

168
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,333
I think that's too much!

169
00:07:28,467 --> 00:07:30,767
No, I lost a husband.

170
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:32,567
I'll drag the whole country
into this

171
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:34,600
if it means getting my revenge,
I'll do it.

172
00:07:34,733 --> 00:07:36,800
I also lost a husband.

173
00:07:36,933 --> 00:07:41,000
But I can never harm
innocent people.

174
00:07:41,133 --> 00:07:42,700
Was he stolen from you?

175
00:07:42,833 --> 00:07:44,033
Charles divorced you, didn't he?

176
00:07:44,167 --> 00:07:45,167
It's not the same.

177
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:49,367
But have you forgotten
our pledge as nurses?

178
00:07:50,467 --> 00:07:51,333
Relax.

179
00:07:51,467 --> 00:07:53,267
As if we're going
to kill people.

180
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,667
We're not murderers.

181
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,067
Actually, we're giving them
a favor

182
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:59,367
to cleanse their digestive
system.

183
00:08:00,233 --> 00:08:02,467
What about the kids
who will eat?

184
00:08:04,033 --> 00:08:05,700
Don't worry,
no kids will eat.

185
00:08:05,833 --> 00:08:08,133
Because we'll make
a spicy sisig.

186
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:11,500
We will tell the adults
that it's not for kids.

187
00:08:11,633 --> 00:08:14,000
We'll give them something else.

188
00:08:14,133 --> 00:08:16,067
But I'm still worried.

189
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:18,733
Many people will get an upset
stomach in that feeding program.

190
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,433
That's good.

191
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,700
The more victims, the merrier.

192
00:08:24,933 --> 00:08:26,933
And if something happens
to them,

193
00:08:27,067 --> 00:08:28,967
Felma will be held accountable.

194
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,800
Help me with this.

195
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:47,533
Oh, Daisy!

196
00:08:47,667 --> 00:08:48,467
Come on.

197
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,867
Come inside.

198
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:50,967
It's okay, Auntie.

199
00:08:52,233 --> 00:08:54,533
Here you go.

200
00:08:59,233 --> 00:09:00,633
This is too much, Auntie.

201
00:09:00,767 --> 00:09:03,367
Tetay only needs 2,000 pesos
for school.

202
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:05,533
Just take it, Dear.

203
00:09:05,667 --> 00:09:07,967
And don't even think about
paying it back, okay?

204
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:10,433
I know your household
expenses went up

205
00:09:10,567 --> 00:09:13,433
when Jeff moved in.

206
00:09:13,567 --> 00:09:15,133
Honestly,
that's not even enough.

207
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,967
I've been meaning to give you
something for a while now,

208
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:21,567
but I didn't want to overstep.

209
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:23,967
Good thing Tetay called me.

210
00:09:25,933 --> 00:09:27,700
Thank you, Auntie.

211
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:31,200
Anyway...

212
00:09:31,333 --> 00:09:34,233
Don't ever hesitate
to come to me

213
00:09:34,367 --> 00:09:36,400
if you need anything, okay?

214
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:38,067
We're family.

215
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:41,067
You're my responsibility too,

216
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:43,000
especially Tetay.

217
00:09:44,433 --> 00:09:47,600
By the way, how's Jeff?

218
00:09:47,733 --> 00:09:49,700
He has a job now.

219
00:09:49,833 --> 00:09:51,833
He's a delivery rider
for Shop Point Express.

220
00:09:51,967 --> 00:09:53,300
Really?

221
00:09:53,433 --> 00:09:55,700
That's nice to hear.

222
00:09:55,833 --> 00:09:57,667
But...

223
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:59,100
that means...

224
00:10:01,533 --> 00:10:03,367
he's not going back to FMP.

225
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:21,200
These are yours.

226
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:36,200
Nice, Bro!

227
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:38,733
Nice welcome
from Shop Point, huh?

228
00:10:38,867 --> 00:10:43,000
Look at that, so many deliveries
in your assigned area.

229
00:10:43,133 --> 00:10:45,733
Hope you get flooded with tips.

230
00:10:45,867 --> 00:10:47,433
Must be beginner's luck.

231
00:10:47,767 --> 00:10:49,000
I hope so, too, Sir.

232
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,000
- Sir, my foot.
- Oh!

233
00:10:51,133 --> 00:10:53,333
- Do you want me to kick you...
- Oh, oh, too serious.

234
00:10:53,467 --> 00:10:54,767
- Go on.
- Come on, this?

235
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:56,867
Yes, that's all yours.

236
00:10:58,367 --> 00:10:59,733
Be careful.

237
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:01,700
Excuse.

238
00:11:03,433 --> 00:11:04,700
Be careful.

239
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,533
Can you do it?

240
00:11:15,867 --> 00:11:17,967
Yes, I can.

241
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:20,033
All right, once you've delivered
all of those,

242
00:11:20,167 --> 00:11:23,400
come back here
for the two high-value parcels.

243
00:11:23,533 --> 00:11:25,033
Got it, Sir.

244
00:11:25,167 --> 00:11:26,400
Sir?

245
00:11:26,533 --> 00:11:28,133
- Newbie?
- Look.

246
00:11:28,267 --> 00:11:29,800
Let's see how long he lasts.

247
00:11:29,933 --> 00:11:32,633
Bet you anything, Jopet,
one week.

248
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:35,933
Come on, don't underestimate
my friend.

249
00:11:36,067 --> 00:11:37,033
Go now.

250
00:11:39,867 --> 00:11:41,300
Jeff, I just need
to make a call.

251
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:42,533
Okay.

252
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:48,867
This is for both of you.

253
00:11:50,767 --> 00:11:51,833
Love you.

254
00:11:54,767 --> 00:11:55,967
Especially you, my daughter!

255
00:11:59,633 --> 00:12:01,300
Miss Martinez, thank you so much

256
00:12:01,433 --> 00:12:03,833
for participating
in the feeding program earlier.

257
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:07,867
Thank you as well,
Ms. Chairwoman.

258
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,667
I was actually hoping this could
become a regular thing.

259
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:10,800
- Oh.
- That's her!

260
00:12:10,933 --> 00:12:12,800
That's the one!
She's the one who served hotdogs

261
00:12:12,933 --> 00:12:15,200
and sisig at the feeding
earlier! That's her!

262
00:12:15,367 --> 00:12:16,533
What's going on?

263
00:12:16,667 --> 00:12:17,833
- That's her!
- Oh, Ms. Chairwoman!

264
00:12:17,967 --> 00:12:19,733
- It's her.
- The people who ate the sisig

265
00:12:19,867 --> 00:12:22,833
she served got food poisoning!

266
00:12:22,967 --> 00:12:25,333
- What?
- Huh? Wait.

267
00:12:25,467 --> 00:12:28,233
Michael, please document this.

268
00:12:28,367 --> 00:12:29,800
You have no shame!

269
00:12:29,933 --> 00:12:33,033
My niece and I have been running
in and out of the bathroom!

270
00:12:33,167 --> 00:12:35,333
Ms. Chairwoman,
can I use your bathroom?

271
00:12:35,467 --> 00:12:36,800
All right, all right!
Over there, go ahead!

272
00:12:37,267 --> 00:12:39,133
See that? Unbelievable.

273
00:12:39,267 --> 00:12:40,333
Wait, wait.

274
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:44,967
Are you sure your stomach pain
was caused by the food

275
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:47,567
Miss Martinez served?

276
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:50,167
that's the reason
why you have a stomach pain?

277
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:53,400
Yes, Ms. Chairwoman.

278
00:12:53,533 --> 00:12:57,433
Yes, that's all my wife,
my sister-in-law, and I.

279
00:12:57,567 --> 00:12:59,600
You poisoned us! You!

280
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:02,300
Where did that sisig come from,
you animal?

281
00:13:02,433 --> 00:13:04,967
Why are so many people
having diarrhea?

282
00:13:05,100 --> 00:13:07,500
Sorry, I don't know anything
about what happened.

283
00:13:07,633 --> 00:13:10,267
My cooking was clean, though.

284
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:13,933
That sisig isn't your ordinary
street food.

285
00:13:14,067 --> 00:13:16,867
<i>"Sisig ni Bunso"
is of high quality.</i>

286
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,433
It's made by FMP.

287
00:13:18,567 --> 00:13:20,033
I'm their distributor.

288
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:22,000
Huh? So it's from FMP?

289
00:13:22,167 --> 00:13:24,600
Hey! FMP!

290
00:13:24,733 --> 00:13:26,867
You scoundrels!

291
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,433
More than thirty people
were food poisoned

292
00:13:29,567 --> 00:13:30,667
from your sisig!

293
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:33,433
Fellow citizens,
I'm warning you.

294
00:13:33,567 --> 00:13:38,400
Don't buy<i> "Sisig ni Bunso"
</i>made by FMP!

295
00:13:42,167 --> 00:13:43,167
Wait, wait.

296
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:45,333
Let's sort this out.

297
00:13:45,467 --> 00:13:48,167
Please don't worry,
I won't run away from this.

298
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:49,533
I'm going to FMP.

299
00:13:49,667 --> 00:13:52,867
I'll talk to them to find out
what really happened.

300
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,333
Why this happened.

301
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:55,600
I'll hold them accountable.

302
00:13:55,733 --> 00:13:56,633
Don't worry.

303
00:13:56,767 --> 00:13:59,167
- That's right!
- Yes, you better!

304
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:00,433
You should feel guilty!

305
00:14:00,567 --> 00:14:02,300
- This is your fault!
- Wait, wait, hold on!

306
00:14:02,433 --> 00:14:03,800
Calm down, calm down.

307
00:14:03,933 --> 00:14:05,700
Please lower your phones.

308
00:14:07,067 --> 00:14:10,100
You heard what Miss Martinez
said, right?

309
00:14:10,233 --> 00:14:12,100
She won't run away from you.

310
00:14:13,333 --> 00:14:17,733
Hopefully, we can talk this
through calmly.

311
00:14:17,867 --> 00:14:21,667
Can I count on you to do
what I'm asking?

312
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:28,233
Take responsibility
for what happened to us...

313
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:30,633
<i> Get ready, Flirty Felma.</i>

314
00:14:30,767 --> 00:14:32,867
<i>You're about to go viral again.</i>

315
00:14:43,567 --> 00:14:45,033
Damn, Bro.

316
00:14:45,167 --> 00:14:46,300
Did you deliver
everything already?

317
00:14:46,433 --> 00:14:48,033
- Yes.
- Show off a little, huh?

318
00:14:48,167 --> 00:14:49,467
No, just excited.

319
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:50,633
Here it is.

320
00:14:50,767 --> 00:14:51,833
Take good care
of those, all right?

321
00:14:51,967 --> 00:14:53,200
That's high-value.

322
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,933
- I will.
- Wait, wait, wait.

323
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:58,033
You dummy, have you eaten yet?

324
00:14:58,167 --> 00:14:59,300
Not yet, later.

325
00:14:59,433 --> 00:15:00,233
I'm dropping this off first.

326
00:15:02,167 --> 00:15:03,033
All right.

327
00:15:03,167 --> 00:15:05,167
But be careful, okay?

328
00:15:06,633 --> 00:15:07,667
Come on, go inside now.

329
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:09,300
Don't forget to eat.

330
00:15:09,433 --> 00:15:11,333
Take care, all right?

331
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,233
My parcel.

332
00:15:36,867 --> 00:15:39,433
You idiot!
Watch where you're going!

333
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:43,767
Jeff!

334
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:45,667
Hey, leave my friend alone!

335
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:46,800
Stop!

336
00:15:47,233 --> 00:15:48,967
That idiot is being arrogant!

337
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:50,433
Sir, you hit me!

338
00:15:50,567 --> 00:15:52,700
- You're the one who's dumb!
- Stop!

339
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:54,200
Calm down!

340
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:55,267
What happened?

341
00:15:55,633 --> 00:15:56,600
My parcel, Jopet.

342
00:16:00,867 --> 00:16:02,567
Is this enough, Friend?

343
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:05,200
Hold, hold back your tears.

344
00:16:05,333 --> 00:16:07,100
Make it fall later.

345
00:16:07,233 --> 00:16:09,167
Later, when you're there.

346
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:10,833
Okay.

347
00:16:10,967 --> 00:16:11,867
All right.

348
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:15,467
I'm ready for my acting debut.

349
00:16:15,833 --> 00:16:16,967
Good luck.

350
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:18,900
Make me proud.

351
00:16:19,033 --> 00:16:21,467
- Are you ready?
- Super ready.

352
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,400
It's showtime!

353
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:35,300
Miss Antonio!

354
00:16:35,433 --> 00:16:36,700
- Yes?
- Miss Antonio!

355
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:38,233
Miss Martinez?

356
00:16:38,367 --> 00:16:39,900
Oh, Miss Martinez, why...

357
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:41,200
Miss Antonio,
we have a big problem.

358
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:42,600
What is it?

359
00:16:42,733 --> 00:16:43,567
Look.

360
00:16:44,733 --> 00:16:45,900
<i> Hey!</i>

361
00:16:46,033 --> 00:16:47,433
<i> FMP!</i>

362
00:16:47,567 --> 00:16:49,700
<i> You scoundrels!</i>

363
00:16:49,833 --> 00:16:52,100
<i>More than thirty people
were food poisoned</i>

364
00:16:52,233 --> 00:16:53,267
<i> from your sisig!</i>

365
00:16:55,533 --> 00:16:58,267
<i>Fellow citizens,
I'm warning you.</i>

366
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:00,100
- What is it?
<i> - Don't buy...</i>

367
00:17:00,233 --> 00:17:03,233
- Paz.
<i>- "Sisig ni Bunso" made by FMP!</i>

368
00:17:04,933 --> 00:17:07,300
I fed people at Luntian Park.

369
00:17:07,433 --> 00:17:10,533
When I was leaving,
a crowd followed me.

370
00:17:10,667 --> 00:17:11,433
What?

371
00:17:11,567 --> 00:17:13,300
Many people
got food poisoning.

372
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:15,833
I told them,

373
00:17:15,967 --> 00:17:20,033
I'd talk to you to find out
what happened with the product.

374
00:17:20,167 --> 00:17:22,233
And that we'd come back to help.

375
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:26,867
But there,
someone posted a video.

376
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:29,467
And it got reposted a lot.

377
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:33,000
I'm scared,
I might get sued.

378
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:34,467
Paz.

379
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:37,500
How did this slip past
our quality control?

380
00:17:37,633 --> 00:17:39,200
Sis, I don't know either.

381
00:17:39,333 --> 00:17:43,567
- God, Sis, this might ruin FMP.
- Oh, my...

382
00:17:44,667 --> 00:17:46,700
So this is where you are,
you shameless lot!

383
00:17:46,833 --> 00:17:47,767
- Come out here!
- Come out here!

384
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:50,600
Hey! Let the owner come out!

385
00:17:50,767 --> 00:17:53,300
Don't block us!

386
00:17:54,467 --> 00:17:55,867
Let us in!

387
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:59,067
Get them out here!

388
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:01,900
- Get them out here!
- Don't block us!

389
00:18:02,033 --> 00:18:03,533
Wait, wait!

390
00:18:03,667 --> 00:18:04,833
Hold on.

391
00:18:04,967 --> 00:18:06,867
- Hold on.
- Will you stop!

392
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,900
You're trespassing,
I can sue you!

393
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:10,067
We'll sue you!

394
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:12,133
Can we please not make
this worse?

395
00:18:12,267 --> 00:18:14,367
Let's sort this out.

396
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:17,233
I understand you're angry,

397
00:18:17,367 --> 00:18:20,433
but I ask for your forgiveness
for what happened.

398
00:18:20,567 --> 00:18:21,900
Don't worry.

399
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:24,633
We will take full
responsibility.

400
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:28,933
The company will cover
all your expenses.

401
00:18:29,067 --> 00:18:32,067
We will also pay you damages.

402
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:34,767
But we need everyone's
cooperation.

403
00:18:37,233 --> 00:18:39,867
Val, accompany them all.

404
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,000
Find out who got food poisoning

405
00:18:42,133 --> 00:18:44,533
so we can check
on their condition.

406
00:18:44,667 --> 00:18:47,200
Is that okay with everyone?

407
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:49,800
Only if you follow through on
everything you just promised us.

408
00:18:51,333 --> 00:18:53,900
Ma'am, please don't leave us
here alone.

409
00:18:54,033 --> 00:18:55,533
Help us.

410
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:58,267
Just make sure
you take responsibility.

411
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:01,500
Keep your promises,
you'll pay us!

412
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:03,233
Do you see all of us here?

413
00:19:03,367 --> 00:19:04,833
We all got stomach pains

414
00:19:04,967 --> 00:19:07,533
because of the food you served.

415
00:19:07,667 --> 00:19:10,300
All right, okay,
we will do everything.

416
00:19:11,333 --> 00:19:12,500
Do we agree?

417
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:16,367
Maybe she's just tricking us.

418
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:18,267
My parcel!
Mister, back the car up!

419
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:21,967
- Pull back! Pull back!
- Pull back! Pull back!

420
00:19:29,333 --> 00:19:31,200
This should still work.

421
00:19:38,367 --> 00:19:39,733
Check the other one, Bro.

422
00:19:39,867 --> 00:19:40,867
Okay.

423
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:44,733
It's broken.

424
00:19:46,333 --> 00:19:47,633
Bro, it's broken.

425
00:19:49,900 --> 00:19:51,800
It wasn't my fault.

426
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:56,333
It's broken.

427
00:19:56,467 --> 00:19:58,833
Can it still be fixed, Bro?

428
00:19:58,967 --> 00:20:00,467
Do you think
it can still be fixed?

429
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,500
We'll find a way.

430
00:20:02,667 --> 00:20:03,767
We'll give it a try.

431
00:20:09,300 --> 00:20:11,433
Bro, it wasn't my fault...

432
00:20:12,767 --> 00:20:15,067
Bro, I was just doing my job...

433
00:20:26,633 --> 00:20:28,300
So? Have you called them yet?

434
00:20:28,433 --> 00:20:29,600
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Ma'am.

435
00:20:29,733 --> 00:20:31,767
Ma'am, many people have already
tagged CPHSO.

436
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:35,033
City Public Health
and Sanitation Office.

437
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:38,300
Oh no, Sis, what now?
What are we going to do?

438
00:20:38,433 --> 00:20:39,700
Should I call Noah?

439
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:42,467
No, let's not bother him, Paz.

440
00:20:44,267 --> 00:20:46,400
We need to act now.

441
00:20:46,533 --> 00:20:51,267
Before CPHSO gets here
and investigates.

442
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:53,333
You know how fast they move.

443
00:20:53,467 --> 00:20:56,233
They might even
show up tomorrow.

444
00:20:56,367 --> 00:20:57,733
- Angge.
- Yes, Ma'am?

445
00:20:57,867 --> 00:20:59,667
Call Atty. Yeban.

446
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:03,800
Tell him to prepare a draft
for a public statement.

447
00:21:03,933 --> 00:21:05,367
Okay, Ma'am.

448
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:09,300
Guys, let's stop production
for now.

449
00:21:09,467 --> 00:21:13,067
Bryan, we need to find out
the batch number

450
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,867
of the stocks we gave
Miss Martinez.

451
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,933
Then, also check
the batches we sent

452
00:21:18,067 --> 00:21:22,067
to the distributors
and resellers, too.

453
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,533
They're starting
to panic, Friend.

454
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:25,867
- We're recalling everything.
- Doesn't seem like it.

455
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:27,100
You call it panicking?

456
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:30,367
The longanisa queen
still looks calm.

457
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:32,167
<i> That's what you think.</i>

458
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:33,900
<i> She's panicking inside.</i>

459
00:21:34,033 --> 00:21:35,900
- Look at her.
- Contamination, spoil...

460
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:40,633
So, she's just pretending?

461
00:21:40,767 --> 00:21:42,067
<i> Yes, Friend.</i>

462
00:21:42,233 --> 00:21:45,000
Looks like she wants
to compete with you

463
00:21:46,033 --> 00:21:48,233
<i>in a showdown
of best acting skills.</i>

464
00:21:48,367 --> 00:21:49,533
Oh, please.

465
00:21:49,667 --> 00:21:51,100
She's got nothing on me, right?

466
00:21:51,233 --> 00:21:52,200
She's just
the supporting actress.

467
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:54,500
I'm the one for best actress.

468
00:21:54,633 --> 00:21:58,333
Don't worry too much
about the bashers

469
00:21:58,467 --> 00:22:01,933
and those claiming
to be victims.

470
00:22:02,067 --> 00:22:05,200
Let's just wait for Val
and Ian to call.

471
00:22:06,667 --> 00:22:08,200
There, Val's calling.

472
00:22:10,367 --> 00:22:11,633
Let's see...

473
00:22:11,767 --> 00:22:16,233
how long you can keep pretending
you're okay, Flirty Felma.

474
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:19,267
This is only the beginning.

475
00:22:20,333 --> 00:22:23,433
Like a movie, we're still
in the opening scene.

476
00:22:23,567 --> 00:22:26,600
The highlight and the finale
haven't even come yet.

477
00:22:26,733 --> 00:22:28,700
There might even be a prequel
and a sequel.

478
00:22:28,833 --> 00:22:30,433
<i>I will talk to them personally.</i>

479
00:22:32,367 --> 00:22:34,833
You ruined my family.

480
00:22:34,967 --> 00:22:37,000
I'll ruin your company, too.

481
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:44,233
Good evening, Ma'am Hazel.

482
00:22:46,333 --> 00:22:48,800
How's the patient in bed 6?

483
00:22:48,967 --> 00:22:50,533
He's still palpitating.

484
00:22:50,667 --> 00:22:52,700
Should I adjust
the dopamine drip?

485
00:22:52,833 --> 00:22:54,267
Is that so?

486
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:57,200
Well, monitor her vitals
every 15 minutes.

487
00:22:57,333 --> 00:22:59,367
If the HR stays above 110,

488
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:00,800
titrate by 2.

489
00:23:00,933 --> 00:23:02,267
Document it right away.

490
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:04,200
Yes, Ma'am. Thank you.

491
00:23:15,533 --> 00:23:18,300
Miss Martinez?

492
00:23:18,433 --> 00:23:20,767
Miss Martinez, I'm so sorry.

493
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:23,700
We didn't know
you were still here.

494
00:23:23,867 --> 00:23:24,933
We were just busy.

495
00:23:25,067 --> 00:23:26,700
We were just dealing with
something about the issue.

496
00:23:27,667 --> 00:23:29,100
No problem, Miss Ruiz.

497
00:23:29,233 --> 00:23:30,500
I understand.

498
00:23:30,633 --> 00:23:33,300
But please understand me, too.

499
00:23:33,433 --> 00:23:35,267
Many people are angry with me.

500
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:38,933
I'm just worried they might come
after me.

501
00:23:39,067 --> 00:23:41,167
Don't worry.

502
00:23:41,300 --> 00:23:43,933
We already have
the full list of victims,

503
00:23:44,067 --> 00:23:45,733
and my staff will visit them.

504
00:23:46,767 --> 00:23:48,000
Don't worry.

505
00:23:48,133 --> 00:23:49,600
You're not part of this.

506
00:23:49,733 --> 00:23:52,033
We'll take full responsibility.

507
00:23:52,167 --> 00:23:53,700
Thank you, Miss Ruiz.

508
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,867
So, what happens now?

509
00:23:58,133 --> 00:24:00,000
We're halting
production for now.

510
00:24:00,133 --> 00:24:04,133
We're preparing for the
sanitation office's inspection.

511
00:24:05,900 --> 00:24:08,000
I'm sorry to hear that.

512
00:24:08,133 --> 00:24:09,967
What if you get shut down?

513
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:12,800
Where else will I get supplies
for my business?

514
00:24:12,933 --> 00:24:15,267
Oh, we're not shutting down.

515
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:17,933
This is the first time something
like this has happened.

516
00:24:18,067 --> 00:24:22,733
In FMP's long history,
this is the first incident.

517
00:24:22,867 --> 00:24:26,667
Our products are clean
and high-quality.

518
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:31,133
Honestly, I feel like
we were sabotaged.

519
00:24:31,267 --> 00:24:32,967
That Hazel.

520
00:24:33,100 --> 00:24:34,667
Hazel?

521
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:36,467
Who's Hazel?

522
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:39,567
Oh, you didn't see
that forest-goblin-looking girl

523
00:24:39,700 --> 00:24:42,600
trashing FMP's website?

524
00:24:42,733 --> 00:24:44,900
Oh, sorry, no.

525
00:24:45,033 --> 00:24:47,100
Oh, long story.

526
00:24:47,233 --> 00:24:49,933
I'll spill the tea another day.

527
00:24:55,167 --> 00:24:56,033
You, too, Sis, right?

528
00:24:56,167 --> 00:24:58,600
That's what you're thinking too?

529
00:24:58,733 --> 00:25:02,033
Of course,
but I don't wanna assume.

530
00:25:02,933 --> 00:25:05,633
Maybe Hazel really had nothing
to do with it.

531
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:08,300
She atoned for her sins.

532
00:25:08,433 --> 00:25:09,633
She humbled herself.

533
00:25:12,567 --> 00:25:13,700
Come on, Sis.

534
00:25:13,833 --> 00:25:15,133
Do you really think

535
00:25:15,267 --> 00:25:18,600
someone like her
can change overnight?

536
00:25:18,733 --> 00:25:22,867
Sis, that woman's body
is overflowing with madness.

537
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:26,033
There's no room left
for goodness to grow.

538
00:25:26,167 --> 00:25:28,000
Sis, seriously.

539
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:32,300
Hold on, I'll take this call.

540
00:25:32,433 --> 00:25:33,567
Okay.

541
00:25:35,767 --> 00:25:37,233
- Hello, Daisy?
- Hey.

542
00:25:37,367 --> 00:25:38,367
Madame...

543
00:25:39,833 --> 00:25:40,833
What?

544
00:25:40,967 --> 00:25:43,333
What happened to my son?

545
00:25:46,067 --> 00:25:47,367
The laptop's broken!

546
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:49,167
The cellphone's broken!

547
00:25:50,367 --> 00:25:52,100
How am I supposed to pay
for all that?

548
00:25:52,233 --> 00:25:53,467
<i> Don't get mad, okay?</i>

549
00:25:53,600 --> 00:25:54,900
But I have a suggestion.

550
00:25:55,033 --> 00:25:56,167
Jopet, don't even start.

551
00:25:56,300 --> 00:25:57,700
I will never go back to FMP,

552
00:25:57,833 --> 00:26:00,533
and I will never ask mom
for help.

553
00:26:00,667 --> 00:26:02,267
Let your mom help you.

554
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:04,633
Mom, I told you!
I don't need your help!

555
00:26:04,767 --> 00:26:06,233
Go back to your new family.

556
00:26:06,367 --> 00:26:07,700
This is all mom's fault.

557
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:09,133
She raised him spoiled.

558
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:11,467
There you go again,
blaming your mom.

559
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:12,533
Don't you know?

560
00:26:12,667 --> 00:26:13,767
Know what?

561
00:26:13,900 --> 00:26:17,000
<i>My fellow citizens,
never ever buy</i>

562
00:26:17,133 --> 00:26:19,800
<i> "Sisig ni Bunso" made by FMP!</i>

563
00:26:19,933 --> 00:26:21,133
- I can handle both.
- I'm here right now...

564
00:26:21,267 --> 00:26:24,433
at the factory and office
of Felma's Food Products,

565
00:26:24,567 --> 00:26:26,467
which was visited earlier
by officials

566
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:29,267
from the City Public Health
and Sanitation Office.

567
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:30,367
Hello, Attorney.

568
00:26:30,500 --> 00:26:33,100
The closure order
has been served.
